 A worker has been injured and rushed to hospital after a factory building in Mobeni East, Durban caught fire. #DStv403 DURBAN - A worker has been injured and rushed to hospital after a factory building in Mobeni East, Durban caught fire. WATCH: Community living in fear after warehouse caught fire The fire has been contained and emergency services are still on the scene with firefighters. Firefighters say the building is now empty but there is much work still to be done. READ: St Francis Bay fire under control "When we arrived we found the building well-ablaze. There is smoke coming out of the building and there are some flames, the fire has been contained to this premises at this stage. That's is the priority for the firefighters," says Robert McKenzie of KZN Emergency Services. Watch the video above for more on this story.